TITLE: Arizona biology teacher sues district over student mask mandate
SUMMARY: An Arizona high school biology teacher has filed a lawsuit against the Phoenix Union High School District arguing that its mask mandate goes against a new state law.

TITLE: Biden admin is 'intimately involved' with critical race theory, former Trump official says
SUMMARY: The Biden administration backtracked on its promotion of a critical race theory group only after officials were “caught with their hand in the cookie jar,” Russ Vought told Fox News in an exclusive interview.

TITLE: Race Imboden displays 'X' on hand during medal ceremony in protest of Olympic rule
SUMMARY: U.S. fencer Race Imboden says that black “X” drawn on the back of his hand after winning the bronze medal in the men’s foil event was a “symbol of solidarity” and was meant to violate the Olympics rule on political demonstrations.

TITLE: Ga. Lt. Gov. Duncan: How we RE-fund our law enforcement agencies without raising taxes or increasing debt
SUMMARY: Our government's most basic responsibility is to keep us safe. In major cities across America that's not happening right now.

TITLE: Texas border city puts up temporary shelters to cope with ‘rapidly escalating’ migrant surge
SUMMARY: The Texas border city of McAllen on Wednesday announced it is setting up temporary emergency shelters in response to what it describes as a "rapidly escalating" surge in migrants flooding across the border — and warning that the numbers are triggering a crisis in the city.

TITLE: Reporter's Notebook: Beware the Ides of August — and maybe December and January too
SUMMARY: The House isn't scheduled to be in session at all this month, but there's a strong likelihood the House will have to return later this month.

TITLE: White House silent on Rashida Tlaib's latest 'anti-Semitic dog whistling' remarks
SUMMARY: Rep. Rahida Tlaib came under fire from ADL president Jonathan Greenblatt for her comments claiming that people working “behind the curtain” to stop a “free Palestine” are “profiting” off Americans.

TITLE: NJ man charged with breaching Capitol, assaulting police officer set to plead guilty
SUMMARY: A New Jersey man indicted for his role in the insurrection at the Capitol in Washington, D.C., on Jan. 6 is set to plead guilty, his attorney said Wednesday.

TITLE: Biden has 'no plans' to call Cuomo to ask for resignation, won't weigh in on New York impeachment: Psaki
SUMMARY: White House press secretary Jen Psaki said Wednesday that President Biden has "no plans" to personally call embattled New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo and ask for his resignation.

TITLE: Leo Terrell: Cuomo vs. Kavanaugh is classic example of 'rules for thee, not for me'
SUMMARY: Fox News contributor Leo Terrell took aim at Governor Cuomo and questioned why the Democratic legislature didn't complete their own investigation when the sexual harassment allegations were made.
